cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with LiDAR odometry, which is an important technology in 3D mapping, autonomous driving, and robot navigation. Additionally, the paper proposes a fully unsupervised Convolutional Auto-Encoder based LiDAR Odometry (CAE-LO) that detects interest points from spherical ring data using 2D CAE and extracts features from multi-resolution voxel model using 3D CAE, which are common techniques used in computer vision. 

The Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category is also likely as the paper deals with autonomous driving and robot navigation, which are key areas of robotics research. 

The Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category is likely as the paper proposes an unsupervised deep learning approach for LiDAR odometry. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is likely as the paper proposes a novel approach for LiDAR odometry that utilizes deep learning techniques. 

The Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with feature extraction and description, which are common tasks in natural language processing.
